#: ../../geovista/docs/src/reference/generated/api/geovista/bridge/index.rst:75
msgid ""
"Defines the topology of each face in the unstructured mesh in terms of "
"indices into the provided `xs` and `ys` mesh geometry arrays. The "
"`connectivity` is a 2D ``(M, N)`` array, where ``M`` is the number of mesh "
"faces, and ``N`` is the number of nodes per face. Alternatively, an ``(M, "
"N)`` tuple defining the connectivity shape may be provided instead, given "
"that the `xs` and `ys` define ``M*N`` points (at most) in the mesh geometry."
" If no connectivity is provided, and the `xs` and `ys` are 2D, then their "
"shape is used to determine the connectivity.  Also, note that masked "
"connectivity may be used to define a mesh consisting of different shaped "
"faces."
msgstr ""

